03\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/area-engine-parity-fixes-2026-03-22.md\n  Description: Applied follow-up parity fixes to the modular area-engine refactor by restoring shouldActivate gating for bright-skip suppression on non-luminance events, ignoring unknown luminance updates, removing dead helpers, and adding regression coverage. Validated with eslint, tsc, and the full targeted vitest suite.\n  Tags: area-engine, bugfix, digital-alchemy, home-assistant, parity, testing\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/area-engine-refactor-implementation-and-review-2026-03-22.md\n  Description: Implemented the Digital Alchemy area-engine modular refactor in the playground repo, added executor/context/plugin architecture and focused tests, then reviewed the implementation and found parity regressions around luminance suppression gating and unknown-state luminance updates. Canary sanity pass was not completed because the HA canary VM was found stopped during validation setup.\n  Tags: area-engine, canary, digital-alchemy, home-assistant, refactor, review, testing\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/area-stateful-scenes-internal-structure-streamlining-2026-03-23.md\n  Description: Follow-up refactor after the initial type colocation work: split area-stateful-scenes engine concerns into events, strategy, plugin registry/evaluation modules, removed the old conditions alias layer, centralized shared HA state-ref adapter logic, tightened exports, and committed/pushed the changes as refactor: streamline area stateful scene internals.\n  Tags: area-stateful-scenes, digital-alchemy, git, home-assistant, module-boundaries, plugins, refactor, typescript\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/area-stateful-scenes-module-boundary-and-plugin-structure-refactor-2026-03-23.md\n  Description: Refactored the Digital Alchemy area-stateful-scenes module to reduce public type surface, colocate types with owning modules, split runtime decision logic into strategy.ts, extract plugin contracts/registry/evaluation into dedicated modules, and centralize shared HA state-ref adapter logic. Validated repeatedly with tsc, lint, and targeted vitest runs while preserving behavior.\n  Tags: area-stateful-scenes, digital-alchemy, home-assistant, module-boundaries, plugins, refactor, testing, typescript\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/digital-alchemy-areas-architecture-and-behavior-model-2026-03-17.md\n  Description: Captured the current canary architecture and behavior model for Digital Alchemy area-based scene orchestration, including room-mode mapping, luminance/away logic, and doc index locations.\n  Tags: home-assistant, digital-alchemy, architecture, stateful-scenes, magic-areas, canary, documentation\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/digital-alchemy-canary-integration-status.md\n  Description: Status log of migration from HA YAML helpers/automations to Digital Alchemy + Synapse entities on canary VM.\n  Tags: digital-alchemy, canary, migration, home-assistant, synapse\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/digital-alchemy-runtime-ops-notes.md\n  Description: Operational notes for running Digital Alchemy persistently in Zellij and env configuration defaults.\n  Tags: digital-alchemy, operations, zellij, home-assistant\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/ha-canary-dashboard-room-card-added-2026-03-18.md\n  Description: Added Office Room Card to canary Home Assistant Lovelace storage dashboards with backups, using the new generic room dashboard contract entities.\n  Tags: home-assistant, dashboard, canary, lovelace, digital-alchemy, room-card\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/ha-proxmox-test-vm-status.md\n  Description: Current state of Home Assistant bare-bones Proxmox test VM setup and operational guardrails.\n  Tags: home-assistant, proxmox, vm, canary, backup, network\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/home-assistant-playground-recovery-and-test-expansion-2026-03-18.md\n  Description: Recovered home-assistant-playground from remote after accidental local deletion, preserved and pushed expanded Digital Alchemy test coverage, and verified prior memory-referenced work exists on remotes.\n  Tags: home-assistant, digital-alchemy, testing, recovery, git, canary\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/hue-scenes-stateful-scenes-integration-feasibility-2026-03-25.md\n  Description: Assessed how Philips Hue scenes could integrate with Stateful Scenes and the Digital Alchemy area-stateful-scenes engine. Found that upstream Stateful Scenes already supports external scene learning for non-Home-Assistant scene entities, which should work for Hue scenes if they appear as scene.* entities in HA, while noting upstream explicitly marks Hue as untested and only tracks limited light attributes. Concluded the preferred path is a canary spike using one static Hue scene learned into a generated switch.*_stateful_scene and then mapped into the existing area engine with no DA engine changes.\n  Tags: home-assistant, hue, stateful-scenes, digital-alchemy, canary, integration, feasibility\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/magic-areas-stateful-scenes-canary-setup-log-2026-03-16.md\n  Description: Session log of installing and validating Magic Areas + Stateful Scenes in HA canary/dev VM, including mock sensors, dashboard debug setup, and WLED office test scene.\n  Tags: home-assistant, canary, magic-areas, stateful-scenes, wled, dashboard, mock-sensors\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/magic-areas-timeout-mode-mapping-and-fork-feasibility-2026-03-18.md\n  Description: Findings on whether Magic Areas supports mode-driven timeout changes via automations and feasibility of forking to add native mode->timeout mapping.\n  Tags: home-assistant, magic-areas, stateful-scenes, timeouts, architecture, fork\n\n- project/home-assistant-playground/migrate-ha-areas-runtime-cutover-2026-04-02.md\n  Description: Captured completion of external runtime wiring, UI control remap, timeout ownership shift, and bridge cleanup fo