{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_end","contentIndex":2,"toolCall":{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mPJhV50uoFO5uRXczrr7xnjM|fc_0ad2abd70cca7d330169de0147fdd48199a0ed6ff0de3b6b21","name":"grep","arguments":{"path":"/home/linkdevk/repos/kg-multicodex/index.ts","pattern":"export function|function |export default","limit":200}},"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating repo refactoring**\n\nI'm considering whether the reference pertains to the current repository before simplification. It seems there's a goal to create a platform-agnostic core based on the existing codebase. Since the current repo is a monolith with tests around the core, I'd need a specification for transforming it into a core + adapter structure. I might consider the source implementation to guide boundaries and behaviors. Also, ensuring behavior parity by referencing existing tests and documentation seems crucial. I'll need to check the current package files for any discrepancies as well.\n\n**Investigating package.json issues**\n\nI noticed that while listing files in the repo root, package.json didn’t appear, which is puzzling since earlier, reading the root package.json was successful. Maybe it’s missing, or the listing command has limitations? I found package-lock.json and Makefile, but not package.json. It seems odd that the read succeeded, suggesting it existed then. Perhaps the listing command uses .gitignore rules, but that seems unlikely. I might need to check the .agents/sources/pi-multicodex for module names, which I've already done.\n\n**Planning the new architecture**\n\nI’m considering whether I need to inspect the README of the source, though it doesn’t seem necessary right now. I think the specification should mention the public interfaces, especially as I plan the file/module layout for the new architecture. Since the user asked about the \"multicodex-core + pi adapter boundaries,\" I’ll likely need to propose n